h3. {color:#205081}Summary{color}
If the user timezone and system timezones are different (and the system's timezone is one day ahead of the user's), JIRA will show the *Release Date* in the *Release Version* popup one day behind the release date in the *Versions* page.

h3. {color:#205081}Environment{color}
* JIRA 6.4.8
* System Timezone: Australia/Sydney
* User Timezone: US/San Fransisco

h3. {color:#205081}Steps to Reproduce{color}
# Navigate to *Administration » System » General Configuration* and set the System Timezone to *Australia | Sydney*.
# Set your user's timezone to GMT-7.
# Add a version with a release date to a project.
# Select the ••• menu and 'Release' next to the version name.

h3. {color:#205081}Expected Results{color}
The release date would be the same as defined in the version release date.

h3. {color:#205081}Actual Results{color}
!release-date.png|thumbnail!

h3. {color:#205081}Original Description{color}
When setting up a version with Release Date of for example Dec 31, 2014.  When trying to Release that date the pop-up model now shows one day prior in version v6.3.13.  Prior versions did not change the release date to 1 day prior to that which has been set.

To track the time worked for the users and availability of the team would be useful if JIRA had a report that shows:
 * Time logged per user;
 * Users that do not have logged time;
 * Report based on a target (if a user should logged 8hrs per day but has not done that). Show only the users that didn't reach the target.

h3. {color:#205081}Summary{color}

JIRA will show the *Release Date* in the *Releases* tab one day behind the actual release date set with the *Release* button in the Kanban Board.
h3. {color:#205081}Environment{color}
 * JIRA v1001.0.0

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Go to the Kanban Board > Click on Release > Click on New Version
 # Create the Version > Click on an issue and add the version into the Fix Version/s:
 # Select the ••• menu and click on the *Releases* tab and it will bring the user to the *Releases* page
 # In the page, when checking the *Release Date*, the day will be shown one day prior to the original date set.

h3. {color:#205081}Expected Results{color}

The release date would be the same as defined in the version release date. If set on 4th August 2017 should show in the release date as 4th August 2017
h3. {color:#205081}Actual Results{color}

!Release_Date_One_Day_Behind.png|width=725,height=154!
h3. {color:#205081}Additional Information{color}
 * An similar ticket regarding this issue had been created and put the status as resolved and fixed: https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-41646

