Error: Unexpected error while restoring data: com.atlassian.studio.host.common.DataSetupException: com.atlassian.studio.host.common.DataSetupException: Error adding user john.smith to group jira-users

h3.Workaround
On the entities.xml remove the line {code}<GlobalPermissionEntry id="XXXXX" permission="SYSTEM_ADMIN" group_id="confluence-administrators"/>{code}

Tempo wrote:

We are facing what I think is a JQL issue, it would be cool it you could have a look at it. Customers are experiencing this and the problem is also visible on our {{tempo-io}} instance. The thing is that we publish team and account options and use them on issues, however the JQL search are not consistent when searching with them.

For example, we have one team linked to one project for which there are multiple issues with this team option. When we search issues with jql `team = "myteam"` it does not find all issues having this team option. I tried re-publishing the options with no luck.

An example of this it `PLAT-564`. This issue has the team option `2`, which has value “Platform Engineering”. However, JQL search with `team=“Platform Engineering” does not return it. But many others issues using the same option are returned as expected. Could you have a quick look and indicate me what could be wrong? Thanks!

when I get the issue, it has this field:
{code:java}
 "customfield_10305": {
      "id": 2,
      "value": "Platform Engineering"
    },
{code}
then this options is (stripped because long, kept relevant parts):
{code:java}
 "projects2": [
        {
          "attributes": [],
          "id": 10301
        },
 ],
 "id": 2,
 "value": "Platform Engineering"
{code}
note that it has alot more projects in `projects2`, all others being
{code:java}
"attributes": [
            "notSelectable"
          ],
         "id": ...
{code}
this is a case with teams, customer reported `account` problems as well.

 
h2. Workaround

Until we solve this issue, there is a workaround available for instances exhibiting the issue. Instead of using option value, we can use id of the option. for e.g.

 
{code:java}
account = aaa{code}
can be changed to
{code:java}
account.id = 2{code}
Where 2 is the id of the option. 

Id of the option can be retrieved either with REST API query, e.g. [https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/#api/2/field/\|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/cloud/#api/2/field/]\{fieldKey}/option-getAllOptions

 or it's in the url of the option configuration screen. For example, on Account configuration screen it's here: 
!option_id.png|thumbnail!
